Read in data. To start, we are focusing on gmpd and pantheria

gmpd <- read_csv(here("data/GMPD_main.csv"))
## Rows: 24323 Columns: 28
## ── Column specification ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## Delimiter: ","
## chr (23): Group, HostReportedName, HostCorrectedName, HostOrder, HostFamily,...

## ℹ Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
## ℹ Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
panth <- read_csv(here("data/panth_subset.csv"))
## Rows: 5416 Columns: 33
## ── Column specification ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## Delimiter: ","
## chr  (2): MSW_Order, MSW_Binomial
## dbl (31): ActivityCycle, AdultBodyMass_g, AgeatEyeOpening_d, AgeatFirstBirth...
## 
## ℹ Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
## ℹ Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
dummy_gmpd <- dummyVars(~ HostOrder, data = gmpd)
gmpd_updated <- as_tibble(predict(dummy_gmpd, newdata = gmpd))
gmpd <- cbind(gmpd, gmpd_updated)
gmpd_dummy_vars <- gmpd %>% dplyr::select(HostCorrectedName, HostOrderArtiodactyla, HostOrderCarnivora, HostOrderPerissodactyla, HostOrderPrimates) %>% distinct()

Measure PSR from gmpd

gmpd_PSR <- gmpd %>% filter(ParType %in% c("Helminth", "Virus")) %>% dplyr::select(HostCorrectedName,ParasiteCorrectedName) %>% 
  distinct() %>% 
  group_by(HostCorrectedName) %>% 
  summarize(psr=n())
gmpd_PSR %<>% inner_join(., gmpd_dummy_vars)
## Joining with `by = join_by(HostCorrectedName)`
panth %<>% mutate(HostCorrectedName = MSW_Binomial)
gmpd_panth <- gmpd_PSR %>% inner_join(panth, by="HostCorrectedName")
gmpd_panth %<>% dplyr::select(-c(HostCorrectedName, MSW_Order, MSW_Binomial))

Use only hosts that overlap between gmpd_panth_macro and gmpd_panth_micro

gmpd_panth_helm_hosts <- gmpd_panth_helm$MSW_Binomial #get all host species from macro database
gmpd_panth_virus_hosts <- gmpd_panth_virus$MSW_Binomial #get remaining host species from micro database
gmpd_panth_arth_hosts <- gmpd_panth_arth$MSW_Binomial
gmpd_panth_bact_hosts <- gmpd_panth_bact$MSW_Binomial
gmpd_panth_proto_hosts <- gmpd_panth_proto$MSW_Binomial

intersect_hosts <- Reduce(intersect, list(gmpd_panth_helm_hosts, gmpd_panth_virus_hosts, gmpd_panth_arth_hosts, gmpd_panth_bact_hosts, gmpd_panth_proto_hosts))

gmpd_panth_helm %<>% filter(MSW_Binomial %in% intersect_hosts)
gmpd_panth_virus %<>% filter(MSW_Binomial %in% intersect_hosts)
gmpd_panth_arth %<>% filter(MSW_Binomial %in% intersect_hosts)
gmpd_panth_bact %<>% filter(MSW_Binomial %in% intersect_hosts)
gmpd_panth_proto %<>% filter(MSW_Binomial %in% intersect_hosts)
gmpd_panth_helm %<>% dplyr::select(-c(HostCorrectedName, MSW_Order, MSW_Binomial))

get_mse <- function(model, test) {
  pred <- predict(model, newdata = test, n.trees = model$n.trees)
  MSE <- mean((pred - test$psr)^2)
  RMSD <- sqrt(mean((pred-test$psr)^2))
  name <- print(substitute(model))
  print(paste("Mean Squared Error for", name,"= ", MSE))
  print(paste("Root Mean Square Deviation for", name, " = ", RMSD))
}
